aestivate, estivate, aestivated, aestivating

1. Said of certain animals: to survive the hot summer months in a [[dormant]] or [[torpid]] state. Comparable to [[hibernate]].

2. Zoology. To pass the summer in a dormant or torpid state.  

3. To spend the summer, as at a special place.

Latin aestvre, aestvt-, from aestvus, estival. See estival